# Stable cluster mapping — rendered into the HCL manifest check.sh feeds
# `hclexp validate -manifest`, so cross-cluster Distributed proxies resolve
# against their target cluster's composition (remote existence + column
# agreement) instead of -skip-validation.
#
# Format:  <cluster_name>  <roles>  [<aliases>]
#   <roles>    comma-separated node roles whose compositions union into the
#              cluster's schema (resolved per -env from ./nodes). Each must be a
#              role in ./nodes.
#   <aliases>  optional comma-separated remote_servers aliases sharing the
#              cluster's schema.
#
# Env-independent: `hclexp validate -env <env>` selects each role's stack, and a
# cluster whose roles aren't composed in that env resolves @absent on its own
# (chschema #127). So the `posthog` data cluster — modeled here only for `local`,
# prod goldens in posthog-cloud-infra — is validated for `local` and absent for the
# cloud envs, from this one declaration, no per-env handling.
#
# `system.*` remotes are always resolvable and need no entry.

ops            ops
logs           logs
aux            aux
ai_events      ai_events
batch_exports  batch_exports
posthog        data           posthog_writable,posthog_primary_replica,posthog_single_shard
